<p><i><b>The Light of Other Days</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/2000" title="2000">2000</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> novel by <a href="/wiki/Arthur_C._Clarke" title="Arthur C. Clarke">Arthur C. Clarke</a> and <a href="/wiki/Stephen_Baxter" title="Stephen Baxter">Stephen Baxter</a>, which explores the development of <a href="/wiki/Wormhole" title="Wormhole">wormhole</a> technology to the point where information can be passed instantaneously between points in the <a href="/wiki/Space-time_continuum" title="Space-time continuum" class="mw-redirect">space-time continuum</a>.</p>
